1
00:00:03,240 --> 00:00:03,900
[SPEAKER_04]: Hi, everyone.

2
00:00:04,221 --> 00:00:11,465
[SPEAKER_04]: Welcome to the subcommittee on school committee considerations of the Medford Charter Study Committee.

3
00:00:13,346 --> 00:00:17,488
[SPEAKER_04]: Tonight, we have with us Ampalit Vanderclute, the facilitator.

4
00:00:18,049 --> 00:00:28,335
[SPEAKER_04]: We have the members, Eunice Brown, Ron Giovino, and Aubrey Webb, and possibly one more member of our subcommittee will be joining us tonight.

5
00:00:29,573 --> 00:00:40,318
[SPEAKER_04]: The purpose of our meeting is to consider the organization of the Medford School Committee as it relates to reviewing the charter of the city of Medford, Massachusetts.

6
00:00:41,618 --> 00:00:47,161
[SPEAKER_04]: So tonight, I thought that we would begin by just talking about the school committee in general.

7
00:00:47,381 --> 00:00:50,842
[SPEAKER_04]: As you know, I was a long-term member of the school committee.

8
00:00:52,663 --> 00:00:56,965
[SPEAKER_04]: And I wanted to review the first order of business was just to kind of look at

9
00:00:57,518 --> 00:01:03,645
[SPEAKER_04]: current organization of the Medford school committee, including election officers and responsibilities.

10
00:01:04,687 --> 00:01:12,696
[SPEAKER_04]: So, as you all know, we have a school committee which has six members, plus the mayor who serves as chair.

11
00:01:13,377 --> 00:01:17,602
[SPEAKER_04]: So altogether there's seven members but we make the distinction because

12
00:01:18,201 --> 00:01:31,964
[SPEAKER_04]: It's six members who elected as school committee members and one member who is elected as the mayor and then as part of her or his responsibilities serves as the chair of the school committee.

13
00:01:32,924 --> 00:01:43,186
[SPEAKER_04]: This is not true in all school committees, but it has been what the way that the Medford School Committee has functioned for a very long time, according to our charter.

14
00:01:44,842 --> 00:01:49,005
[SPEAKER_04]: Also, as you all know, we hold elections every two years.

15
00:01:50,666 --> 00:01:57,149
[SPEAKER_04]: And the entire school committee plus the mayor is up for election at the same time.

16
00:01:57,810 --> 00:02:01,412
[SPEAKER_04]: This is also not true in some other cities and towns.

17
00:02:01,928 --> 00:02:06,229
[SPEAKER_04]: where they might have staggered elections.

18
00:02:06,389 --> 00:02:12,851
[SPEAKER_04]: So part of the school committee is elected at one time, or they might have differing term lengths.

19
00:02:13,671 --> 00:02:18,332
[SPEAKER_04]: The purpose of that would be to ensure that there was always some continuity.

20
00:02:20,393 --> 00:02:25,694
[SPEAKER_04]: Luckily, it hasn't been in the 32 years that I've served plus the two years since then,

21
00:02:26,279 --> 00:02:31,989
[SPEAKER_04]: The issue of continuity has not been a big issue for us because there's always been some members going forth.

22
00:02:32,570 --> 00:02:38,400
[SPEAKER_04]: But that is why, you know, it is a concern in some communities.

23
00:02:41,257 --> 00:02:46,880
[SPEAKER_04]: As a school committee member, I already said that it took two years to learn what you were doing.

24
00:02:47,601 --> 00:03:00,187
[SPEAKER_04]: So the first two years, you really were learning what you were doing and getting your understanding the whole scope of the position and how to do.

25
00:03:00,608 --> 00:03:01,668
[SPEAKER_04]: Hey, Phyllis, how are you?

26
00:03:01,728 --> 00:03:02,068
[SPEAKER_04]: Welcome.

27
00:03:03,009 --> 00:03:03,369
