41
00:03:37,187 --> 00:03:41,432
[SPEAKER_04]: I mean, I think sort of everybody kind of knows but I want to give a general

42
00:03:43,228 --> 00:03:44,809
[SPEAKER_04]: sense of what the school committee does.

43
00:03:46,571 --> 00:03:56,698
[SPEAKER_04]: And I looked on the MASC website, and just so that I can read it, I don't have it posted for you, but I'm going to give you some, the outline.

44
00:03:57,639 --> 00:04:12,830
[SPEAKER_04]: And this is on, MASC is the organization, Massachusetts Association of School Committees, that school committee members have as a resource, as a backup, as the place that you go when you need some help and

45
00:04:14,235 --> 00:04:15,195
[SPEAKER_04]: clarifications.

46
00:04:15,896 --> 00:04:24,441
[SPEAKER_04]: There is, I served at some point as did Anne Marie Cunha was the president so Medford has had a representation on the statewide association.

47
00:04:25,422 --> 00:04:25,822
[SPEAKER_04]: There is a

48
00:04:27,995 --> 00:04:35,084
[SPEAKER_04]: conference every year which in fact is happening right now where school committee members from across the Commonwealth come and get together.

49
00:04:35,104 --> 00:04:45,436
[SPEAKER_04]: It's invaluable because you get to learn about other districts and what problems they're facing and you become less insular in your own

50
00:04:46,377 --> 00:04:53,961
[SPEAKER_04]: understanding of your school committee activities and all the issues that are faced by school committees across the Commonwealth.

51
00:04:54,502 --> 00:04:57,703
[SPEAKER_04]: So this is from them, and I think it's very comprehensive.

52
00:04:59,024 --> 00:05:04,267
[SPEAKER_04]: And I'm going to just give you a quick rundown of what a school committee does.

53
00:05:08,729 --> 00:05:11,470
[SPEAKER_04]: First, the school committee is a policymaking

54
00:05:13,958 --> 00:05:15,960
[SPEAKER_04]: form a role.

55
00:05:16,501 --> 00:05:24,470
[SPEAKER_04]: And it is the role of the school committee to make the policy and to review the policies for the school district.

56
00:05:25,811 --> 00:05:29,215
[SPEAKER_04]: And that's really how you govern, you govern by making policies.

57
00:05:30,757 --> 00:05:48,730
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee has an important finance role where they review and approve a budget for education in the district according to a process and timeline developed with the superintendent and the mayor and what other governs our particular city.

58
00:05:50,271 --> 00:05:52,953
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee appoints the superintendent.

59
00:05:54,829 --> 00:06:07,158
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee also appoints the assistant or associate superintendents, the school business administrator, the administrator of special education, school physicians, and registered nurses.

60
00:06:08,996 --> 00:06:17,804
[SPEAKER_04]: And we also appoint our own legal counsel and supervisors of attendance.

61
00:06:17,824 --> 00:06:27,734
[SPEAKER_04]: And they are the superintendent makes a recommendation and the school committee then appoints those particular positions.

62
00:06:29,954 --> 00:06:39,059
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee also sets compensation levels for the superintendent and overall compensation limits for other positions.

63
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:43,838
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee has a very important role in collective bargaining.

64
00:06:44,638 --> 00:06:53,605
[SPEAKER_04]: They act as the employer of school employees for school collective bargaining purposes, and they designate a negotiator or a negotiating team.

65
00:06:54,486 --> 00:07:09,157
[SPEAKER_04]: There are times when the school committee becomes part of that negotiation team, but that's usually, you know, hopefully you might have settled your contract before that becomes a more active role.

66
00:07:11,371 --> 00:07:18,216
[SPEAKER_04]: And we receive advice from the superintendent about the educational consequences of different bargaining positions.

67
00:07:19,436 --> 00:07:27,942
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee establishes upon recommendation of the superintendent, the performance standards for teachers and other employees of the school district.

68
00:07:28,923 --> 00:07:39,791
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee evaluates the performance of the superintendent, and that's outlined very carefully in mass general laws on how that is to be done.

69
00:07:42,496 --> 00:07:52,381
[SPEAKER_04]: It also does a self-evaluation to evaluate the effectiveness of the school committee itself.

70
00:07:53,302 --> 00:08:02,887
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee has a role in professional development and adopts a professional development plan for all principal, teachers, and other professional staff.

71
00:08:07,013 --> 00:08:14,481
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee receives and approves annual school improvement plans for each school in the district.

72
00:08:17,584 --> 00:08:19,826
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee has a role in advocacy.

73
00:08:20,667 --> 00:08:27,935
[SPEAKER_04]: We engage in advocacy on behalf of students and their schools and promote the benefits of a public school system to the community.

74
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:39,046
[SPEAKER_04]: A school committee has a role in curriculum, approve major adoptions or revisions of curriculum and textbooks upon the recommendation of the superintendent.

75
00:08:40,947 --> 00:08:51,353
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee establishes educational goals and policies for the schools in the district consistent with the requirements of law and the statewide goals and standards established by the Board of Education.

76
00:08:53,517 --> 00:09:00,599
[SPEAKER_04]: The school committee supports the development and promotion of the vision, mission, goals, and strategies of the school committee.

77
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:15,103
[SPEAKER_04]: School committee members consult and confer with the superintendent on all matters as they arise that concern the school system and on which the school committee may take actions.

78
00:09:19,449 --> 00:09:24,553
[SPEAKER_04]: And the school committee supports the superintendent in all matters that conform to committee policy.

79
00:09:25,594 --> 00:09:32,399
[SPEAKER_04]: So I think that those are really gives you a summary of the scope of school committee responsibilities.

80
00:09:33,259 --> 00:09:34,520
[SPEAKER_04]: Anybody got any questions?

81
00:09:36,282 --> 00:09:37,182
[SPEAKER_04]: Yeah, Phyllis.

