00:34:09,492 --> 00:34:10,653
[SPEAKER_06]: OK, and Phyllis?

298
00:34:11,994 --> 00:34:16,078
[SPEAKER_06]: Yeah, one of my big concerns, well, I have two major areas.

299
00:34:18,079 --> 00:34:21,482
[SPEAKER_06]: I find it challenging to have parents be involved.

300
00:34:22,503 --> 00:34:32,651
[SPEAKER_06]: I hear people here saying that parents want more involvement, but it's always been my experience that we can't get parents to be involved.

301
00:34:33,112 --> 00:34:34,813
[SPEAKER_06]: They're too busy, rightly so.

302
00:34:34,873 --> 00:34:36,695
[SPEAKER_06]: This is not a criticism toward parents.

303
00:34:37,508 --> 00:34:47,292
[SPEAKER_06]: But one of my main reasons of wanting to be part of this subcommittee is that I'm not really sure the place of the mayor on the school committee or the role of the mayor in the school committee.

304
00:34:47,652 --> 00:34:50,814
[SPEAKER_06]: I think that's a big issue and concern for me.

305
00:34:52,614 --> 00:34:59,838
[SPEAKER_06]: And the second thing is that I wanted to learn more about the role of the school committee in relationship to the school.

