320
00:35:59,250 --> 00:36:00,331
[SPEAKER_06]: Well, for the charter study.

321
00:36:00,844 --> 00:36:01,665
[SPEAKER_04]: For the charter study.

322
00:36:01,705 --> 00:36:09,032
[SPEAKER_04]: So to get input from her about how the interactions with city council and school committee and how it affects her position.

323
00:36:09,652 --> 00:36:09,932
[SPEAKER_04]: Okay.

324
00:36:11,113 --> 00:36:11,414
[SPEAKER_04]: Okay.

325
00:36:11,754 --> 00:36:14,136
[SPEAKER_01]: Can I just make a point though?

326
00:36:15,157 --> 00:36:26,548
[SPEAKER_01]: Paulette, I know you have a longstanding relationship with her as a former member, but it shouldn't take that

327
00:36:27,665 --> 00:36:30,548
[SPEAKER_01]: to get a response from the super.

328
00:36:31,148 --> 00:36:38,315
[SPEAKER_01]: We've been, the 11 or 12 of us have been appointed by the mayor to do very important work in the city.

329
00:36:39,175 --> 00:36:44,840
[SPEAKER_01]: And we're all residents and we're all invested in one way or the other in the school system.

330
00:36:44,920 --> 00:36:49,725
[SPEAKER_04]: But Eunice, I understand where you're going, but- It shouldn't take having you step in.

331
00:36:50,905 --> 00:36:57,188
[SPEAKER_04]: I understand that, but at the same time, the superintendent's primary responsibility is to the children of the district.

332
00:36:57,648 --> 00:37:04,612
[SPEAKER_04]: And if she hasn't quite figured out, you know, the importance of this particular committee, give her a break.

333
00:37:05,252 --> 00:37:11,935
[SPEAKER_04]: I mean, you know, if I now go to her and sort of say, hey, this is what's going on and we really need your input, could you make time?

334
00:37:13,116 --> 00:37:17,758
[SPEAKER_04]: But I'm not gonna, I'm certainly not gonna hold her feet to the fire because she hasn't done it yet.

335
