[SPEAKER_04]: You know?

336
00:37:18,727 --> 00:37:28,450
[SPEAKER_06]: So the other thing I thought, Paulette, was that perhaps she didn't know that this was, you know, maybe she didn't know her place in this also and couldn't find a way to figure that out.

337
00:37:28,510 --> 00:37:29,791
[SPEAKER_06]: That's one thing I thought.

338
00:37:30,191 --> 00:37:37,113
[SPEAKER_06]: I mean, I think for me, the critical piece is that we have to keep our eye on the real reason for the problem, the school system.

339
00:37:37,253 --> 00:37:38,113
[SPEAKER_06]: It's for our students.

340
00:37:38,373 --> 00:37:44,175
[SPEAKER_06]: You know, all this, we can get things straight in our own way, but I think that's really important.

341
00:37:44,716 --> 00:37:53,718
[SPEAKER_04]: I think we also need to fully understand that it's not our role to criticize school committee members, the superintendent, that's not our role.

342
00:37:55,399 --> 00:37:58,319
[SPEAKER_04]: I understand why it's coming up, but that's not our role.

343
00:37:59,339 --> 00:38:13,943
[SPEAKER_04]: And what our role is to say, how is the school committee functioning and is there anything that we are suggesting that goes in the charter so to assure that it's functioning better?

344
00:38:15,111 --> 00:38:17,933
[SPEAKER_04]: Remember, superintendents change and school committee members change.

345
00:38:18,553 --> 00:38:28,659
[SPEAKER_04]: So it's really, you're thinking about this without specifics, whether you're frustrated with the superintendent or not, or frustrated with school committee members or not.

346
00:38:28,919 --> 00:38:32,141
[SPEAKER_04]: How should it be working to be the most effective?

347
00:38:32,741 --> 00:38:32,921
[SPEAKER_06]: Right.

